### Describe the bug

First of all, I don't know, if it's really a bug. At least it could lead to performance problems.

I used the default server-side blazor template and added a cascadingvalue with two custom components (C1, C2).

```razor
<p role="status">Current count: @currentCount</p>

<button class="btn btn-primary" @onclick="IncrementCount">Click me</button>

<CascadingValue Name="Counter" Value="currentCount">
    <Component1>
        <Component2></Component2>
    </Component1>
</CascadingValue>
```

Component1:
```razor
<h3>Component1 @Counter</h3>

@ChildContent

@code {
    [CascadingParameter(Name = "Counter")]
    public int Counter { get; set; }

    [Parameter]
    public RenderFragment ChildContent { get; set; }

    private int dbgCounter;
    protected override void OnParametersSet()
    {
        Console.WriteLine("C1: " + ++dbgCounter);
    }
}

```

Component2:
```razor
<h3>Component2: @Counter</h3>
   
@code {
    [CascadingParameter(Name = "Counter")]
    public int Counter { get; set; }

    private int dbgCounter;
    protected override void OnParametersSet()
    {
        Console.WriteLine("C2: " + ++dbgCounter);
    }
}

```

#### Behavior:
If I click on the increment button, then OnParameterSet is called on C1, then on C2 and it's called once again on C1.

I assume that C1 is called, because C2 is a RenderFragment-Parameter of C1 and this RenderFragment (C2) is changed on C1 through the cascading-value. Is this assumption right? If it's right, do you think it performs good? Couldn't it be better, to set the cascading-value from buttom-up (C2, C1), instead of top-down (C1, C2)?

### Expected Behavior

If I click on the increment button, then OnParameterSet should only get called once on C1

